WEBVTT

00:00.072 --> 00:01.449
What's the big surprise?

00:02.025 --> 00:03.723
I'm finally going to do it.

00:03.912 --> 00:05.544
I'm gonna take the plunge.

00:07.023 --> 00:09.593
Oh my God!
You're going to buy a cell phone?

00:09.617 --> 00:10.929
No, beeper.

00:11.749 --> 00:12.818
A beeper?

00:13.380 --> 00:16.420
- It's all you need.
- No, Mr. Monk uses beeper anymore.

00:16.491 --> 00:18.615
- They are former history.
- Dr. Kruger has one.

00:18.789 --> 00:21.818
Well, except for doctors. Doctors
use them because they work anywhere

00:21.943 --> 00:24.741
- They are more reliable.
- Reliable is good. That's what we want.

00:25.117 --> 00:27.278
So when you are out with Julie,
or you are on a date,

00:27.293 --> 00:29.235
- I can beep you.
- Hold on, hold on!

00:30.345 --> 00:31.618
The beeper's for me?

00:31.927 --> 00:34.412
Yeah, it's only $29 a month,
you can afford it.

00:34.493 --> 00:37.980
And you want me to pay for it?
That's your big surprise.

00:38.192 --> 00:40.374
Are you.
Are you surprised?

00:40.599 --> 00:42.586
You know what's kinda sad?
I'm not.

00:43.698 --> 00:44.743
Sorry.

00:45.749 --> 00:48.635
Over there, Mr. Monk.
That couple over there.

00:48.971 --> 00:52.145
He's been on the news all week,
their daughter was murdered.

00:52.492 --> 00:54.518
Mr. Monk, they're staring at you.

00:54.711 --> 00:57.534
I think they want to hire you.
They want you to solve the case.

00:57.549 --> 00:58.553
No, thank you.

00:58.568 --> 01:01.144
Mr. Monk, you can't say no.
This was their daughter.

01:01.318 --> 01:03.427
You know how busy I am.
I'm doing my tags,

01:03.449 --> 01:05.381
I'm rotating the coach, cushions,

01:05.827 --> 01:07.705
I'm just going to tell them
I can't do it.

01:11.374 --> 01:13.303
They are gonna start crying, right?

01:13.458 --> 01:14.750
Probably.

01:15.387 --> 01:18.011
They are gonna show me
pictures of their daughter,

01:18.667 --> 01:22.481
pictures of her when she was a kid,
pulling a little red wagon.

01:23.277 --> 01:26.303
Probably a dog in the wagon,
there's always a dog.

01:26.692 --> 01:28.329
Then, they going to start begging,

01:28.624 --> 01:30.859
offering me all the 
money they have,

01:31.225 --> 01:33.478
and they just get to go on,
and on, and on...

01:33.540 --> 01:36.616
police can't do anything,
you're the only one who could help us.

01:37.303 --> 01:39.789
The crying and the weeping
and the pleading.

01:41.418 --> 01:42.769
Okay, fine.

01:43.116 --> 01:44.602
Fine, you win!

01:44.891 --> 01:46.550
I'll take the case.

